{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"enhanced-panoramic-armedcrab","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why / Summary\n\nThe inbound link differ maps Jira `Blocks` issuelinks to the INVERTED rebar relation\n(`blocks`<->`depends_on`). Latent since f6687adf4 (2026-06-15); UNMASKED when the\noutbound direction fix (6b25dbead/43d154523) corrected the write path — the two\ninversions had been cancelling on round-trip. Result: ~815 inbound link applies/pass\nare cycle-rejected by rebar's guard, and the reconciler never converges.\n\n## Root cause (proven, LIVE-validated)\n\n- `_diff_links_inbound` (inbound_differ.py:519-527) AND `_diff_link_removals`\n  (outbound_links.py:198-203) both invert inward/outward -> relation.\n- LIVE Jira ground truth: REB-458 (\"0250 blocks ba7e\") carries `outwardIssue: REB-461`\n  with `type.outward == \"blocks\"`. So **outwardIssue+Blocks => rebar `blocks`;\n  inwardIssue+Blocks => rebar `depends_on`.** The code does the OPPOSITE (verified by\n  running the current `_diff_links_inbound` on real REB-461 JSON — it emits the\n  cycle-causing inverse).\n\n## Chronic-pattern guardrails (this fix MUST NOT repeat prior failures)\n\nPrior link fixes (3f04, c8ed, 3b86) each corrected ONE seam and were validated by a\nROUND-TRIP / self-consistency oracle that is invariant under double inversion — so the\nmirror stayed broken and every audit read through the inversion. This fix must:\n\n- [ ] Fix BOTH mirror sites in lockstep (inbound add AND removal path).\n- [ ] UNIFY the duplicated direction logic into ONE helper (the inward/outward->relation\n      mapping is copy-pasted in inbound_differ.py and outbound_links.py; `_JIRA_LINK_TO_RELATION`\n      is re-declared in acli_graph.py:53, inbound_differ.py:459). One source of truth so the\n      next inversion cannot reappear on an untouched copy.\n- [ ] Assert ABSOLUTE direction pinned to a captured LIVE-JIRA ground-truth fixture\n      (real REB-458/461 issuelinks JSON), NOT round-trip agreement. A test that asserts\n      \"outbound<->inbound agree\" is banned here — it passes on inverted code.\n\n## The completeness requirement (a pure branch-swap is NOT sufficient)\n\nMeasured on 17 real tickets: a pure swap eliminates the 30 cycle-rejections but then\nemits ~all MIRROR-adds (the counterpart already owns the edge; ~400 spurious deps\nstore-wide). The fix must add INVERSE-AWARE CROSS-TICKET dedup: emit an inbound link\nonly if the edge X<->Y is absent in rebar in EITHER equivalent form (X has (blocks,Y)\nOR Y has (depends_on,X); and the relates_to symmetric case). `compute_inbound_mutations`\nalready receives `local_tickets_by_id`, so the counterpart's deps are available.\n\n- [ ] The dedup map MUST include the FULL local set (incl. archived tickets) — a residual\n      mirror to archived cf10 in the live prototype was ONLY a map-exclusion artifact;\n      cf10 owns the inverse edge. Verify `local_tickets_by_id` completeness or the fix\n      re-emits mirrors to archived counterparts.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Local ticket A has dep `A blocks B`; both bound to Jira; outbound has (correctly)\n   written REB-A outward Blocks -> REB-B.\n2. Run inbound diff (or a reconcile pass).\n3. Observe: inbound emits `A depends_on B` (inverted) -> rebar cycle-guard rejects it\n   (\"would create a cycle\"). Expected: 0 inbound emits (edge already synced).\n\n- Expected: inbound emits 0 link mutations for an already-synced link (either direction).\n- Actual: inbound emits the inverted relation, cycle-rejected every pass.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A `_diff_links_inbound` unit test on the CAPTURED LIVE REB-458 issuelinks JSON\n      (outwardIssue Blocks) asserts relation == `blocks`; on REB-461 JSON (inwardIssue\n      Blocks) asserts relation == `depends_on`. RED on current code. Proving command:\n      `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/ -k link_direction -q`.\n- [ ] A `_diff_links_inbound` test with the counterpart owning the inverse edge asserts\n      0 emitted mutations (inverse-aware dedup). RED on a pure-swap fix.\n- [ ] The removal-path mirror (`_diff_link_removals`) has an equivalent absolute-direction\n      test. RED on current code.\n- [ ] Existing tests that encode the reversed convention (test_reconcile_roundtrip.py:522,\n      test_link_dedup.py:198) are corrected to the live-Jira shape and pass.\n- [ ] LIVE fix-verification (pre-land): the fixed inbound differ, run against real REB\n      issuelinks for the ~815 affected pairs, emits 0 cycle-rejecting mutations and 0\n      mirror-adds (prototype already validated: converges to 0 with the full local map).\n- [ ] `make test` passes; no new external dependency.\n\n## Notes\nP2 of epic 58b0. Blocked-independent of P1. The observability promotion (separate child)\nshould land AFTER this so the reconciler isn't flipped to fail-loud while this noise exists.","id":"4b59-3bf9-d4a4-4768","parent_id":"58b0-104b-777c-4227","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Inbound link differ inverts blocks<->depends_on (unmasked by outbound fix); needs inverse-aware cross-ticket dedup"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784318289317003001,"uuid":"25bf29fa-b6f8-4bcc-b128-8cc77c064dfc"}